5.  Environment and safeguard specialist (national 4 person-months). The environment 
and safeguard specialist will contribute mainly to outputs 1 and 2. Tasks are to 

(i)  review national and provincial laws, policies, and standards for environmental 
protection;  
(ii)  review the status of energy consumption in the selected industries, i.e., iron and 
steel, power generation, chemicals, building materials, and non-ferrous metals; 
(iii)  analyze the selected industries and review their production technologies and 
emissions reduction status;  
(iv)  estimate major emissions of the selected industries, i.e., CO , sulfur dioxide, 
2
nitrous oxides, particulates, etc., and identify major emissions sources; 
(v)  compare the selected industries with corresponding international and national 
emissions reduction benchmarks and identify their potential to reduce emissions; 
(vi)  help the team leader draft the investigation report; 
(vii)  help the team leader draft the EE&ER strategy and recommended action plan;  
(viii)  help the training specialist identify training requirements and develop training 
materials on safeguards. 

6.  Training specialist (national 3 person-months). The training specialist will contribute to 
output 3. Tasks are to 

(i)  become familiar with the TA objectives and training requirements;  
(ii)  work  with  other  consultants  to  schedule  training  programs,  seminars,  and 
workshops; 
(iii)  work with other consultants to develop training materials, workshop and seminar 
proceedings, and presentation handouts;  
(iv)  work with other consultants to identify international and national participants for 
seminars and workshops, as well as prepare invitation letters, as directed by the 
Yunnan provincial government and ADB; and 
(v)  summarize  seminars  and  workshops  and  training  results  and  report  to  the 
Yunnan provincial government and ADB. 

B.  Reporting Requirements 

7.  The consultants will submit (i) an inception report within 1 month after signing the 
